{{Infobox artwork | image_file = John William Waterhouse - The Favorites of the Emperor Honorius - 1883.jpg | title = The Favourites of the Emperor Honorius | artist = [[John William Waterhouse]] | year = 1883 | medium = [[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | material = | height_metric = 117 | width_metric = 202 | metric_unit = cm<!--don't leave this parameter blank—either don't include it, or include the default cm. Not including it will default it to cm.--> | city = Adelaide | museum = [[Art Gallery of South Australia]] | owner = }} [[File:John William Waterhouse - The Favorites of the Emperor Honorius - 1883 (study).jpg|thumb|Study for ''The Favourites of the Emperor Honorius'']]
'''''The Favourites of the Emperor Honorius''''' is a painting by [[John William Waterhouse]] completed in 1883.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.johnwilliamwaterhouse.com/pictures/favourites-emperor-honorius-1883/|title=johnwilliamwaterhouse.com: The Favourites of the Emperor Honorius|accessdate=15 January 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121126234038/http://www.johnwilliamwaterhouse.com/pictures/favourites-emperor-honorius-1883/|archivedate=26 November 2012|df=}}</ref> The painting depicts [[Honorius (emperor)|Honorius]] feeding birds which are on the rug in front of him; the dark colors of the rug and his clothes define a space. Separated from him and the birds are the councillors seeking his attention, and who along with the attendant are dressed in paler shades.<ref name="Hobson">Hobson, Anthony. 1989. ''J. W. Waterhouse''. Oxford: Phaidon Christie's. pages 25, 28-29. {{ISBN|0-7148-8066-3}}</ref>
''The Favourites of the Emperor Honorius'' is part of the collection of the [[Art Gallery of South Australia]], which also owns Waterhouse's ''[[Circe Invidiosa]]''.<ref>[http://www.artgallery.sa.gov.au/agsa/home/Collection/european_and_north_american_paintings_and_sculpture.html Art Gallery of South Australia: Collection]</ref>
